have you seen https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/OEM_SCHEMAS.md ?

This is going to require a lot more explanation than it currently has before this is going to get accepted into bmcweb. Why can't this be standard Redfish? Have you engaged the DMTF? What does this OEM do and why do we need it?

yes, we have already proposed in DMTF and created PR.
Plan to use these OEM schemas until DMTF PR gets approved & released by DMTF

Please wrap at 50/72. See https://cbea.ms/git-commit/. 
I have noticed I have made this comment in several of your commits (e.g. https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/53959). Maybe set your editor up so you don't have to manually do this? 

E.g. 

 .vimrc for commit messages:

  autocmd Filetype gitcommit  setlocal textwidth=72 tabstop=2 shiftwidth=2 expandtab spell
